{"created": "2025-01-23T17:02:43.043512+00:00", "modified": "2025-05-23T08:59:11.305301+00:00", "id": 14727277, "conceptrecid": "11472536", "doi": "10.5281/zenodo.14727277", "conceptdoi": "10.5281/zenodo.11472536", "doi_url": "https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.14727277", "metadata": {"title": "A dataset of laymen olfactory perception for 74 monomolecular odors", "doi": "10.5281/zenodo.14727277", "publication_date": "2025-01-23", "description": "<p>The molecular structure of an odor determines whether and how it is perceived by humans. However, the principles of how &nbsp;odorant chemistry links to perceptual patterns remain largely unknown and are primarily studied using odor rating datasets from highly trained olfactory experts, such as perfumers. This limits our knowledge of typical odor perception and its variability over individuals. We provide a dataset featuring free descriptions, evaluative ratings, and qualitative labels for 74 chemically diverse mono-molecular odors, rated by a large sample of young adults. A total of 1,227 participants described and rated the odors, and completed questionnaires covering their demographic background, personality traits, and the role of olfaction in their daily lives. The dataset offers a valuable foundation for research aimed at understanding the fundamentals of olfactory perception.</p>", "access_right": "open", "creators": [{"name": "Bierling, Antonie Louise", "affiliation": "Friedrich Schiller University Jena", "orcid": "0000-0003-3372-1106"}, {"name": "Croy, Alexander", "affiliation": "Friedrich-Schiller-Universit\u00e4t Jena", "orcid": "0000-0001-9296-9350"}, {"name": "Jesgarzewsky, Tim Lukas", "affiliation": null, "orcid": "0000-0003-1163-2102"}, {"name": "Rommel, Maria", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Cuniberti, Gianaurelio (Giovanni)", "affiliation": "Technische Universit\u00e4t Dresden", "orcid": "0000-0002-6574-7848"}, {"name": "Hummel, Thomas", "affiliation": null, "orcid": "0000-0001-9713-0183"}, {"name": "Croy, I